originalText.text: I went here before covid and it was one of the worst service experiences I have ever had. I have never left a bad review in my life. But after a year I’m still thinking about this experience. I came into the salon and I simply wanted to get my acrylic nails soaked off. The man ended up using his metro card to take off the acrylics and broke all of my real nails to the point that I was bleeding after I left. Even though he could see how disappointed I was, he charged me for the service anyway and I left the place astonished by what happened. I don’t get my nails done often so I did not know what to expect but when I got to work later in the day I told my coworkers about it and they were astonished. I’m honestly still shocked by the whole thing to this day.
